properties.designation: Marine Conservation Zone; OSPAR Marine Protected Area
properties.purpose: Marine Conservation Zones (MCZs) protect typical, rare or declining habitats and species found in the seas of the UK. This site provides additional protection in this area for the spiny lobster. The species is being protected because the number of spiny lobsters has been falling, particularly in areas of South-west England.
properties.restrictions:
1. No person shall use in fishing for sea fish or shellfish any harpoon spear or like instrument.
2. When diving, it is prohibited to remove crab, lobster, or scallops from a fishery.
3. It is prohibited to operate any vessel using mobile fishing gear, with exceptions.
4. It is prohibited to use pots for fishing within the District without an authorized permit.
5. The removal or disturbance of shellfish during temporary shellfish fishery closures is prohibited.
properties.allowed: Other types of fishing and activities may be permitted in accordance with applicable regulations.
properties.managing_authority: Department for Environment, Food & Rural Affairs; Joint Nature Conservation Committee; Natural England; OSPAR Commission
properties.regulation_name: Devon and Severn Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority Byelaw Booklet, October 2018
